2821	[Geometric pullback-square iso over a preimage cover member]
2822	  \label{def:pullback_preimage_iota_iso}
2823	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.pullbackPreimageιIso}
2824	  \uses{lem:modules_pullback_mathlib}
2825	  \textit{Pseudofunctoriality iso realising the commuting preimage square.}
2826	  Let \(g : Y \to X\) be an open immersion, \(M\) a sheaf of modules on \(X\), and \(U \subseteq X\) an
2827	  open with preimage \(g^{-1}(U)\). Writing \(k : g^{-1}(U).\mathrm{toScheme} \to U.\mathrm{toScheme}\) for
2828	  the open immersion induced by \(g\) (so \(k \circ U.\iota = (g^{-1}U).\iota \circ g\)), the
2829	  pseudofunctoriality of pullback (\(\mathrm{pullbackComp}\)) gives a natural isomorphism
2830	  \[
2831	    \bigl((g^{-1}U).\iota^{*}\bigr)\,(g^{*}M) \;\cong\; k^{*}\bigl(U.\iota^{*}\,M\bigr) .
2832	  \]
2833	\end{definition}
2834	\begin{proof}
2835	  \uses{lem:modules_pullback_mathlib}
2836	  Compose the pullback-composition coherence isos along the two ways of reading
2837	  \((g^{-1}U).\iota \circ g = k \circ U.\iota\): \(\mathrm{pullbackComp}\,k\,U.\iota\), the congruence
2838	  \(\mathrm{pullbackCongr}\) of the square identity, and \((\mathrm{pullbackComp}\,(g^{-1}U).\iota\,g)\)
2839	  inverted. Each is an instance of the \(\mathrm{pullbackComp}\) pseudofunctoriality of the pullback of
2840	  sheaves of modules (\cref{lem:modules_pullback_mathlib}).
2841	\end{proof}
