2843	\begin{definition}\leanok
2844	[Presentation of the pullback's geometric restriction to a preimage cover member]
2845	  \label{def:presentation_pullback_iota_preimage}
2846	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.presentationPullbackιPreimage}
2847	  \uses{def:presentation_pullback_iota_of_quasicoherentData, lem:presentation_map_mathlib,
2848	    lem:modules_pullback_mathlib, def:pullback_preimage_iota_iso, def:pullback_open_immersion_unit_iso}
2849	  \textit{For an open immersion $g$, the pulled-back sheaf has a presentation on the geometric
2850	  restriction to each preimage cover member.}
2851	  Let \(g : Y \to X\) be an open immersion, \(M\) a sheaf of modules on \(X\) with quasi-coherence data
2852	  \(q\), and \(i\) a cover index. Write \(N := (\mathrm{pullback}\,g).\mathrm{obj}\,M\) and
2853	  \(W_i := g^{-1}(q.X_i)\). Then the geometric restriction
2854	  \((W_i.\iota^{*})\,N\) admits a \(\mathrm{SheafOfModules.Presentation}\) on \(W_i.\mathrm{toScheme}\).
2855	\end{definition}
2856	\begin{proof}
2857	  \uses{def:presentation_pullback_iota_of_quasicoherentData, lem:presentation_map_mathlib,
2858	    lem:modules_pullback_mathlib}
2859	  The open immersion \(g\) restricts to an open immersion
2860	  \(k : W_i.\mathrm{toScheme} \to (q.X_i).\mathrm{toScheme}\) on preimages, characterized by the
2861	  commuting square \(k \circ (q.X_i).\iota = W_i.\iota \circ g\) (the morphism induced by \(g\) between
2862	  the inclusion of \(W_i = g^{-1}(q.X_i)\) and that of \(q.X_i\)). By pseudofunctoriality of pullback
2863	  (\(\mathrm{pullbackComp}\), named in prose) this square gives a natural isomorphism
2864	  \[
2865	    (W_i.\iota^{*})\,N \;=\; (W_i.\iota^{*})\,(g^{*}M)
2866	      \;\cong\; (W_i.\iota \circ g)^{*}M
2867	      \;=\; (k \circ (q.X_i).\iota)^{*}M
2868	      \;\cong\; k^{*}\bigl((q.X_i).\iota^{*}\,M\bigr) .
2869	  \]
2870	  Now \((q.X_i).\iota^{*}\,M\) carries the geometric presentation
2871	  \cref{def:presentation_pullback_iota_of_quasicoherentData}. Apply \(\mathrm{Presentation.map}\)
2872	  (\cref{lem:presentation_map_mathlib}) along the pullback functor \(k^{*}\)
2873	  (\cref{lem:modules_pullback_mathlib}), which preserves colimits and carries the unit sheaf to the
2874	  unit sheaf, to obtain a presentation of \(k^{*}\bigl((q.X_i).\iota^{*}\,M\bigr)\); transport it across
2875	  the displayed isomorphism via \(\mathrm{Presentation.ofIsIso}\) to land a presentation of
2876	  \((W_i.\iota^{*})\,N\).
2877	\end{proof}
